        "data": {
            "key": "IEIGXJH3",
            "version": 64594,
            "itemType": "journalArticle",
            "title": "Лесные мыши Северного Кавказа и Предкавказья.",
            "creators": [
                {
                    "creatorType": "author",
                    "firstName": "G. A.",
                    "lastName": "Свириденко"
                }
            ],
            "abstractNote": "This study presents the results of investigations on forest mice (Sylvaemus = Apodemus) of the Northern Caucasus and Fore-Caucasus. These species are poorly studied but are of considerable theoretical and practical importance because many of them are serious pests of orchards, vineyards, forest plantations, and agricultural crops. The material is based on a large collection of specimens gathered by the author and collaborators in the North Caucasus between 1925–1930, supplemented with comparative collections from Prof. S. I. Ognev and the Zoological Museum of Moscow State University. The fauna of the region proved to be rich in species, including new forms. The paper provides taxonomic descriptions, distributional records, and notes on ecology, reproduction, and economic significance of several taxa, including Sylvaemus sylvaticus ciscaucasicus, S. s. mosquensis, S. fulvipectus (with new subspecies saxatilis and planicola), S. flavicollis samaricus, and S. flavicollis ponticus. Emphasis is placed on variation in external measurements and coat coloration, reproduction cycles, and the role of these rodents as agricultural pests.",
