            "abstractNote": "Mammal trapping efforts were conducted during the summer and fall of 2014 at sites in five counties in Texas (Delta, Fayette, Hopkins, Lubbock, and Dickens). These efforts resulted in 18 county records involving: one soricomorph, one chiropteran, one lagomorph, one cingulate, and ten species of rodents. The species record for Microtus extends the range substantially southward into the central region of the Llano Estacado in Texas. These records expand our knowledge of the distribution and occurrence of mammals in Texas.",
